menu "breadboard: bb_diag_http (bb_diag's aggregate HTTP surface)"

config BB_DIAG_ROUTES
    bool "Build bb_diag HTTP routes"
    default y
    depends on BB_DIAG_PANIC_CAPTURE
    help
        When enabled, bb_diag_http registers the legacy exact-route HTTP
        handlers: GET/DELETE /api/diag/boot, GET/DELETE /api/diag/panic,
        GET /api/diag/coredump, GET /api/diag/heap, GET /api/diag/tasks,
        and GET /api/diag/sockets. Relocated verbatim from bb_diag (B1-1153)
        -- same symbol name, same behavior, only ownership moved.

config BB_DIAG_PANIC_TRIGGER
    bool "Expose POST /api/diag/panic/trigger to force a panic (debug only)"
    default n
    depends on BB_DIAG_ROUTES
    help
        When enabled, bb_diag_http exposes POST /api/diag/panic/trigger which
        deliberately dereferences a null pointer to force a LoadProhibited
        panic. Used to validate panic capture / coredump end-to-end on bench
        hardware without physically rebooting the device. NEVER ship to
        production: any unauthenticated caller can crash the firmware.

config BB_DIAG_SECTIONS
    bool "Build the generic /api/diag/* section registry (wildcard dispatch)"
    default y
    help
        When enabled, bb_diag_sections_init() registers a GET /api/diag/*
        wildcard route dispatching to whichever section a caller has
        registered via bb_diag_register_section() (bb_diag). Independent of
        BB_DIAG_ROUTES (the legacy exact-route panic/coredump handlers) --
        this registry is a separate, generic seam that will eventually
        replace those handlers section by section. The portable registry
        itself (bb_diag_register_section, bb_diag) always builds regardless
        of this option; only this component's ESP-IDF wildcard-route
        dispatcher is gated.

endmenu
